data.description: Modern country living within easy driving distance of Kansas City. Located in west-central Cass County near Cleveland is this beautiful, secluded 21.22-acre farm. The property is located 7 minutes from 69 HWY and approximately 25 minutes from Overland Park Kansas. The 6 bedroom and 4 bathrooms home is nestled among the creeks and woods creating a quiet sanctuary. This is an earth contact home with ground floor living with a heat pump, central air, and a mother-in-law’s quarters with a private entrance built above allowing plenty of room to stretch out. Everything on the first floor has been remodeled with warm modern finishes, lots of storage, and an open-concept kitchen and dining room with built-in custom buffet. The kitchen has custom cabinets, granite countertops, a gas stove, and a large island with seating for three. There is a bonus room and a very large laundry room just off of the kitchen. The large master bedroom has space for a king bed along with a large ensuite and walk-in closet. Three of the other rooms are all generous in size with large closets and could be bedrooms, offices, or any purpose you need. The remaining two rooms are non-conforming bedrooms that could be used for any purpose. This home is 4153 square feet, was built in 1982, and is well-maintained with many upgrades and improvements. Outside the front door is a nice covered porch, patio area, and a four-car carport. The large 40X30 shop is only a few years old and has a 10-foot overhang, concrete floors, power, and lights. Further back on the property is a large hay barn for even more storage. The property has two spring feed creeks and one seasonal creek. There are nice mature stands of timber running along all three creeks providing privacy and great habitat for wildlife. The large field to the east has been allowed to grow up and become brushy for improved wildlife habitat. There are always turkeys and deer in the field behind the house.
